The paper deals with the design of a stream cipher, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR). The cipher is based on algebraic structures and involves polynomial equations, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of quasigroups and string transformations also suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DS). Finally, the comparison of the speed of the proposed cipher with other symmetric-key stream ciphers suggests a connection to systems and control theory (cs.SY).
